sentences: Pierre Bensusan (born 30 October 1957) is a French-Algerian acoustic guitarist.
Born in 1957 in Oran, French Algeria he moved to Paris with his family when he was four years old.
Born in 1957 in Oran, French Algeria he moved to Paris with his family when he was four years old.
Four years later, he began to teach himself guitar after his father had bought him a steel string acoustic guitar and a classmate taught him "a few chords".
He has stated that he became interested in playing in DADGAD because of its "mystical" and "romantic" quality which made him feel like he had gone back to the 16th or 17th century.

In 2006, Bensusan contributed his song "Falafel a Montsegur" to the album Artists for Charity â€“ Guitarists 4 the Kids, produced by Slang Productions, to assist World Vision Canada in helping underprivileged children.
Intuite (Favored Nations, 2001) was his first instrumental, solo acoustic guitar album.
